D. Scott Neal Inc. Reduces Position in Pepsico, Inc. (NYSE:PEP)

Posted by Tim Parker on Jul 25th, 2017 // No Comments 

D. Scott Neal Inc. cut its position in Pepsico, Inc. (NYSE:PEP) by 2.8% during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The fund owned 938 shares of the company’s stock after selling 27 shares during the period. D. Scott Neal Inc.’s holdings in Pepsico were worth $105,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
Other hedge funds have also bought and sold shares of the company. Franklin Resources Inc. increased its position in shares of Pepsico by 2.2% in the fourth quarter. Franklin Resources Inc. now owns 15,671,152 shares of the company’s stock valued at $1,639,677,000 after buying an additional 340,666 shares during the last quarter. Norges Bank purchased a new position in shares of Pepsico during the fourth quarter valued at approximately $1,492,411,000. Bank of Montreal Can increased its position in shares of Pepsico by 16.6% in the first quarter. Bank of Montreal Can now owns 5,812,519 shares of the company’s stock valued at $650,189,000 after buying an additional 827,376 shares during the last quarter. Fisher Asset Management LLC increased its position in shares of Pepsico by 0.9% in the first quarter. Fisher Asset Management LLC now owns 5,497,671 shares of the company’s stock valued at $614,970,000 after buying an additional 50,154 shares during the last quarter. Finally, Teachers Advisors LLC increased its position in shares of Pepsico by 3.4% in the fourth quarter. Teachers Advisors LLC now owns 2,866,110 shares of the company’s stock valued at $299,881,000 after buying an additional 94,391 shares during the last quarter. Hedge funds and other institutional investors own 70.45% of the company’s stock. 




Pepsico, Inc. (PEP) opened at 116.13 on Tuesday. The stock has a market capitalization of $165.54 billion, a P/E ratio of 24.59 and a beta of 0.68. The firm’s 50-day moving average is $116.03 and its 200-day moving average is $111.61. Pepsico, Inc. has a 52 week low of $98.50 and a 52 week high of $118.24. 


 Get Pepsico Inc. alerts:



Pepsico (NYSE:PEP) last posted its earnings results on Tuesday, July 11th. The company reported $1.50 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, beating analysts’ consensus estimates of $1.40 by $0.10. The company had revenue of $15.71 billion for the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $15.57 billion. Pepsico had a return on equity of 59.74% and a net margin of 10.77%. The firm’s quarterly revenue was up 2.0% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period last year, the business posted $1.35 earnings per share. On average, equities research analysts predict that Pepsico, Inc. will post $5.16 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
The business also recently announced a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Friday, September 29th. Shareholders of record on Friday, September 1st will be paid a $0.805 dividend. This represents a $3.22 dividend on an annualized basis and a yield of 2.77%. The ex-dividend date is Wednesday, August 30th. Pepsico’s payout ratio is 68.22%. 
WARNING: “D. Scott Neal Inc. Reduces Position in Pepsico, Inc. (NYSE:PEP)” was published by BNB Daily and is the sole property of of BNB Daily. If you are reading this piece on another website, it was illegally stolen and reposted in violation of United States and international copyright laws. The original version of this piece can be accessed at https://www.baseball-news-blog.com/2017/07/25/pepsico-inc-nysepep-stake-cut-by-d-scott-neal-inc-updated.html. 
PEP has been the topic of several analyst reports. UBS AG upgraded shares of Pepsico from a “neutral” rating to a “positive” rating in a report on Wednesday, April 12th. Susquehanna Bancshares Inc upgraded shares of Pepsico from a “neutral” rating to a “positive” rating and upped their target price for the stock from $118.00 to $132.00 in a research note on Wednesday, April 12th. Zacks Investment Research downgraded shares of Pepsico from a “hold” rating to a “sell” rating in a research note on Tuesday, April 18th. Jefferies Group LLC upped their price target on shares of Pepsico from $120.00 to $127.00 and gave the stock a “buy” rating in a research report on Wednesday, April 19th. Finally, Royal Bank Of Canada set a $115.00 target price on shares of Pepsico and gave the company a “hold” rating in a research report on Monday, April 24th. Five analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating, fourteen have assigned a buy rating and one has given a strong buy rating to the company’s stock. Pepsico has a consensus rating of “Buy” and an average target price of $123.04.
About Pepsico
PepsiCo, Inc is a global food and beverage company. The Company’s portfolio of brands includes Frito-Lay, Gatorade, Pepsi-Cola, Quaker and Tropicana. The Company operates through six segments: Frito-Lay North America (FLNA), Quaker Foods North America (QFNA), North America Beverages (NAB), Latin America, Europe Sub-Saharan Africa (ESSA), and Asia, Middle East and North Africa (AMENA). 

 
