About MeI am a Certified Financial Planner and the founder and CEO of D. Scott Neal, Inc., a fee-only financial planning and SEC-registered investment advisory firm. We help people make informed, intelligent decisions with their money at any stage of life. Prior to creating the firm, I practiced as a CPA. 
I am the author of over 100 articles in MD Update, a publication for doctors, and a contributor to the book, Wealth Strategies for Doctors.
I am a veteran of the U.S. Army having served 4 years on active duty in Nurnberg, Germany and an additional 6 years in the U.S. Army Reserve. I attained the rank of Captain. 
I hold two masters degrees, a MBA with emphasis in accounting and a Master of Divinity with emphasis in Pastoral Care. 
